      <h2 id="inventory">Master inventory</h2>
      <p>
        The canonical catalog with every URL, destination and status is at
        <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/INVENTORY.md"><code>source/INVENTORY.md</code></a>.
        Updated whenever new material is captured.
      </p>

      <h2 id="notInArchive">Things explicitly <em>not</em> in the archive</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>WordPress source code</strong> for openpropdata.org.uk — the site uses commercial themes/plugins; only the rendered HTML is mirrored.</li>
        <li><strong>Member-confidential commercial documents</strong> — none of OPDA's internal commercial agreements with members or vendors are stored here.</li>
        <li><strong>Personal data</strong> — transcripts are heavily redacted where they touch consumer information.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="howToBrowse">How to browse</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/resource.html">resource viewer</a> reads any path under
        <code>source/</code> and renders it inline — JSON via JSON Crack, Markdown
        and text as plain text in an iframe, PDFs in the browser's PDF viewer,
        images natively, and so on. Pre-bundled JSON wrappers under
        <code>docs/data/resources/</code> let it work over <code>file://</code> as
        well as <code>http://</code>.
      </p>

      <h2 id="subPages">Sub-pages</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="81-document-archive.html"><strong>Document archive</strong></a> — every report, deck and project document, catalogued</li>
        <li><a href="82-transcript-archive.html"><strong>Transcript archive</strong></a> — video + meeting transcripts in one place</li>
        <li><a href="83-external-references.html"><strong>External references</strong></a> — gov.uk, NTS, related standards</li>
      </ul>

